7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both HubSpot Operations Hub and Make (Integromat) share a solid foundation of core features including Visual Builder, Code Support, Api Connections, Scheduling. On the other hand, Make (Integromat) uniquely offers Ai Actions, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, HubSpot Operations Hub holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Make (Integromat) scores 9/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both HubSpot Operations Hub and Make (Integromat) offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. HubSpot Operations Hub's free tier and Make (Integromat)'s free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
